history.text: Hello
Have you seen Zootopia before?
Hello
Yes, I have.  I enjoyed it.
We watch it probably once a week or so. My kids really like it.
According to the document, it got really good reviews, too.
I like the part on the document how it has looking past stereotypes. That's a good lesson.
Yeah, I would say 98% on rotten tomatoes is really good- because that review system can be quite harsh.
Yeah, I was surprised by how intelligent the movie was about social issues.
I agree.  Rotten Tomatoes has a bit too much power these days.
Yes, I have looked up movies before and was shocked to see how low some of the reviews were.
My page just switched, but it's still about Zootopia.
Yeah, it will be more of the document. I believe 2 more "rounds" of this document.
So now we can see the cast/intro stuff.
My page looks the same tho lol usually it's more stuff.
I also see a "key scene" bit.  I forgot about the going "savage" bit of the movie.
I don't think I knew that Jason Bateman was the voice of the fox.
OH yeah. the savage part. I always forget about that part, its a little dark to see, but my kids didn't think much of it.
My favorite part was probably the sloth part.
It helps me not to know the voice actor.  that takes me out of the movie when i recognize the celebrity
that's a good point!  I kind of dont like knowing either.
My document advanced
yeah, new scene added.  the asylum bit is mentioned.  another dark element.
Yes that was a creepy part too
lot of important themes.  but not preachy if i remember right
I agree. They were sort of just vague things- but not really thrown in your face.  That makes it better.
I think that is why my kids do not get bored with this movie - OR the secret life of pets lol
I wonder if they will make a part 2 for this movie.
maybe the riskiest bit was combining themes of racism with a police story.  it was brave to address that together.
I didn't even think of it like that- pretty brilliant and like ya said, risky.
i would watch a sequel
my document screen is blank now.
oh no- mine has a 3rd section  talking about when judy goes back to nick and they reconicle
then they head to that subway train where the drugs were being developed by the night howlers

Judy and Nick obtain the serum as evidence, but before they can reach the ZPD,
Bellwether confronts them in the Natural History Museum and takes the evidence,
revealing herself as the mastermind behind a prey-supremacist conspiracy. Judy and
Nick are trapped after Nick refuses to abandon an injured Judy. Bellwether shoots a
serum pellet at Nick to make him kill Judy, and summons the ZPD for help, but Judy
and Nick have replaced the serum pellets in Bellwether's gun with blueberries.
Enraged, Bellwether threatens to frame the pair for the attacks, but Judy has recorded
Bellwether's confession. Bogo and the ZPD arrive and Bellwether is arrested.
oh yeah.  the subway bit is creepy
